Operation Dudula, the movement known for targetting foreigners in its campaigning, has launched in Rustenburg, in the North West. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports. Courtesy #DStv403 RUSTENBURG - Operation Dudula, known for being outspoken about foreigners living in south africa, chose Freedom Day to launch in Rustenburg in the North West. Operation Dudula leaders say the community needs their support in fighting crime. eNCA's Heidi Giokos shares more details in the video above.